<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Best of BBC: Actress Margot Kidder will serve as host of an anthology series, 
"Best of the BBC," beginning Sunday night on the Discovery Channel. Kidder will 
introduce the new one-hour series, which will serve up a wide range of 
subjects, including "America," Alistair Cooke's 12-part personal history of the 
United States and winner of four Emmys. Also featured will be "The Making of a 
Continent," a six-part series. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
