<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: ANDERSON SHARES TOURNAMENT LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Craig Anderson of Fallbrook and Bill O'Connor of Beverly Hills shot eight-under 
par 64s to take the first-round lead Tuesday in the Trans-Mississippi Four-Ball 
Championship at The Farms Golf Club in Rancho Santa Fe. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Duncan of Rancho Santa Fe and Randy Reznicek of Vista shot 68s and trail by 
four strokes. 
</P>
<P>
The second round will be played today, followed by the final round on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Todd Bernard scored with 18 minutes remaining off an assist from Mark Vogel to 
give host Point Loma Nazarene College a 1-1 tie with 12th-ranked The Masters 
College in a nonconference game. PLNC is 2-3-1. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
UC Riverside defeated host UC San Diego, 15-6, 16-14, 11-15, 15-8, in a 
nonconference game. Vicki Van Duyne had 16 for UCSD (18-4) kills. Shandi Byrd 
had 14 kills for UC Riverside, which is 7-3 and ranked third in Division II. 
</P>
<P>
USIU defeated host Point Loma Nazarene College, 15-8, 15-2, 15-12, in a 
nonconference match. Debbie Simpson led PLNC (11-5) with 13 kills. Heather 
Kelly led USIU (6-9) with 13 kills and April Devine had 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
