<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Doug Moe Jr., formerly a Denver Nuggets' assistant coach under his father, sued 
the first black owners of a major sports franchise, claiming he was fired 
because he is white. 
</P>
<P>
The civil complaint against the Denver Nuggets Limited Partnership alleges the 
"acts in terminating were without cause and were motivated, in part, by 
consideration of race." 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit filed in Denver District Court alleges that the firing constituted 
breach of contract because the younger Moe received oral assurances he would be 
signed to a new one-year contract worth $80,000 for this season. 
</P>
<P>
The Nuggets have since hired Paul Westhead as coach and Jim Boyle as an 
assistant. Both are white. 
</P>
