<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BRADLEY, BARRETT NAMED TOP WSC PLAYERS ON OFFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freddie Bradley of Moorpark College and Jeff Barrett of Santa Monica have been 
named the Western State Conference's co-offensive players of the week. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley rushed for 205 yards in 19 carries and scored three touchdowns in a 
41-10 victory over Valley on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Barrett, a sophomore from Burroughs High, completed 16 of 21 passes for 302 
yards and five touchdowns in a 53-26 victory over Compton. Barrett was named 
the conference's offensive player of the week the previous week. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge women's volleyball team will take on U.S. International in 
San Diego tonight at 6. The Matadors (10-5) are coming off a three-game sweep 
of the University of San Diego in which Marianne Dixon had 17 kills and six 
blocks. USIU is 4-9. 
</P>
<P>
Right-side hitter Shelly Swalec is doubtful for tonight's match because of a 
strained muscle. 
</P>
<P>
"We feel like we're ready, tactically," CSUN Coach Walt Ker said. "The key for 
us tonight is to execute. Our outside hitting has been a bright spot, but it's 
also been inconsistent." 
</P>
<P>
Greg Seiler has resigned as Cal Lutheran sports information director to take a 
similar position at Mars Hill College in Mars Hill, N. C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
