<LENGTH>
<P>
96 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jet Engine Cracks Probed: Cracks inside the shafts of 12 Pratt &amp; Whitney 
PW4000 jet engines have prompted a Federal Aviation Administration 
investigation, with findings expected to be released next week. The defective 
shafts cleared inspections at Pratt in Hartford, Conn., and at Le Fiell Co., 
the San Francisco-based subcontractor that forged the shafts for Pratt, the 
Hartford Courant reported. One engine had been in service before it was 
grounded, three had been shipped for installation on jumbo passenger jets and 
the others were in various stages of assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
