<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATWATCH: CRUSADERS FORCED TO GO EXTRA YARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Village Christian High tied a school record for first downs in a 21-13 loss to 
Murphy, but the circumstances could have been better for the Crusaders. 
</P>
<P>
They were forced to gamble when the team's only long snapper, Billy Rust, 
suffered an ankle injury early in the third quarter. Coach Mike Plaisance, not 
wanting to risk special-teams turnovers, forsook the punt six times on 
fourth-down situations in the second half. Village Christian got the first down 
five times and made 19 overall to tie the record set at Santa Fe Christian in 
1985. 
</P>
<P>
Special teams: Kennedy kicker Keith West booted a school-record 50-yard field 
goal in Kennedy's 36-0 defeat of Franklin last week. West, an All-City Section 
soccer player, easily bettered the old mark of 43 yards. 
</P>
<P>
"It would have been good from 57 yards, easy," Kennedy Coach Bob Francola said. 
"It landed halfway across the track and cleared the uprights." 
</P>
<P>
Beginnings: Royal, which has matched its school record (set in 1969 and first 
equaled in '75) with its 3-0 start, has outscored its opponents, 94-13. . . . 
Grant is 2-0 behind a strong defense. The Lancers have picked off four passes, 
including two by Hillsdale Hufanga. Grant has allowed an average of 32 yards 
rushing. . . . If nothing else, Verdugo Hills (0-2) is showing consistency. The 
Dons gained four yards total offense in each of their losses. 
</P>
<P>
Defense: Kennedy linebacker Damon Tice has 18 solo tackles and has caused two 
fumbles in two games. . . . San Fernando defensive back Amon Flanagan, a 
sophomore, has 5 1/2 sacks in two games. . . . Cornell Hill, a senior defensive 
back at Taft, made eight solo tackles and recorded two sacks in a 28-0 defeat 
of Hamilton. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Streaks: Birmingham, which will play Reseda on Thursday in a battle for Victory 
Boulevard bragging rights, has not defeated the Regents since 1979. Reseda is 
12-0-1 against Birmingham over that span. 
</P>
<P>
Passing: Westlake's Todd Preston attempted 51 passes this season before he 
threw an interception Thursday against Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley attempted just one pass in its 17-16 win over Redlands. The 
ground-oriented Antelopes have thrown the ball just 18 times in three games. 
</P>
<P>
Ends: Rio Mesa's Jamie Liddell (seven receptions for 214 yards) is averaging 
more than 30 yards a catch. . . . Westlake's Erik Holcomb (nine receptions for 
220 yards) is averaging more than 23 yards a catch. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
