<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
2 KILLED IN VAN FIRE IN COMPTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COMPTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two members of a Latin band died and a third man was critically burned today 
when their van caught fire. 
</P>
<P>
The flames spread to destroy a house, leaving a dozen people homeless, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire apparently started about 1:10 a.m. in the van, which was parked in the 
driveway of a house in the 500 block of North Poinsettia Avenue, Lt. Steve 
Roller said. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters and police arrived to find both the van and the house fully 
engulfed in flames, he said. When the van fire was extinguished, officers 
discovered three men inside the charred vehicle, Roller said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
